The '''Impeachment Union''' ({{lang-hy|Իմպիչմենթ դաշինք}}) was a [[political party]] in [[Armenia]]. In the [[Armenian parliamentary election, 2007|2007 Armenian parliamentary elections]] it won no seats, but won a popular vote of 1.29%. This union leader is [[Nikol Pashinyan]]. This union's goal was the [[impeachment]] of the then president [[Robert Kocharyan]]. Dissolved in 2008, after nomination of [[Levon Ter-Petrosyan]] of candidate in [[Armenian presidential election, 2008|Armenian presidential election]], and after merged into Levon Ter-Petrosyan's led [[Armenian National Congress]].
