'''Inventors Assistance League''' (IAL) is a non-profit organization created to assist [[inventors]], small businesses and entrepreneurs. Its parent organization, the National Inventor's Foundation, was the very first federally chartered [[non-profit]] group to serve creative individuals since [[patent laws]] were established in 1790.<ref>[http://www.inventions.org/ Inventors Assistance League Website]</ref>{{rs|date=October 2015}}{{fv|date=October 2015}}

[[Entrepreneur|Founder]] and original president [[Ted De Boer]] was a [[patent]] agent with [[United States Copyright Office|US Trademark and Copyright Office]]. He created the [[organization]] in 1962 (and formalized with the State of California in 1970) when he became frustrated with the lack of affordable [[legal advice]] and guidance for inventors.<ref>[http://www.easimedia.com/mtree/resource_directory/hobbies/inventors/inventors_assistance_league/details/]</ref>{{fv|date=October 2015}}

The organization helps individuals file for a [[trademark]] or patent, file for a [[copyright]], learn to [[Marketing|market]] their inventions and get Pre-Patent Protection.<ref>[http://www.inventions.org/about/index.html IAL Site] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081028233859/http://www.inventions.org/about/index.html |date=October 28, 2008 }}</ref>{{fv|date=October 2015}}

The [[Better Business Bureau]] rates the Inventors Assistance League with an A+ Rating, its highest possible rating.<ref>[http://www.la.bbb.org/BusinessReport.aspx?CompanyID=21559 BBB Ratings]</ref> The Inventors Assistance League has its office in [[Los Angeles]] ([[Eagle Rock, Los Angeles|Eagle Rock]]), [[California]].<ref>[http://search.bbb.org/Results.aspx?n=Inventors+Assistance+League&add=&c=&st=&z= IAL Offices]</ref>

