{{Politics of Nagorno-Karabakh}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in the unrecognised [[Republic of Artsakh|Nagorno-Karabakh Republic]] on 20 February 2017. At least 25% of registered voters needed to vote in favour in order to validate the result. The referendum passed with about three quarters of voters voting.<ref name=DD>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=az012017 Nagorno-Karabakh (Azerbaijan), 20 February 2017: Constitution] Direct Democracy {{de icon}}</ref>
==Background== President [[Bako Sahakyan]] created a commission to draft a new constitution to replace the [[Constitution of Nagorno-Karabakh|2006 constitution]]. The draft was delivered on 24 November 2016 and approved by the [[National Assembly (Nagorno-Karabakh Republic)|National Assembly]] on 17 January by a vote of 20–7.<ref name=DD/> On 19 January, Sahakyan set the referendum date.<ref name=DD/>
==Constitutional changes== The constitutional changes would result in the name "Artsakh Republic" being officially adopted for the unrecognised country and used alongside its current name, as well as in abolishing the office of the [[Prime Minister of the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic|Prime Minister]] and giving more power to the [[President of the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic|President]] to make quicker decisions on security.<ref>[https://euobserver.com/foreign/136961 Referendum to create 'Republic of Artsakh' on Europe's fringe] EU Observer, 20 February 2017</ref>
Levon Galustyan, an MP from the unrecognised country of [[Abkhazia]] and an observer at the referendum, said the idea for a name change was brought forward after Nagorno-Karabakh politicians had expressed worry that the use of the name "Artsakh" and "Nagorno-Karabakh" by Azerbaijan for its athletic teams and artistic initiatives abroad might create the wrong impression of the region's reality.<ref>[http://sputnik-abkhazia.ru/press_center/20170223/1020477493/galistian-ideia-pereimenovania-abhazii-v-apsni-mne-simpatichna.html Галустян: идея переименования Абхазии в Апсны мне симпатична] Sputnik, 23 February 2017</ref>
==Results== {| class=wikitable style=text-align:right !Choice !Votes !% |- |align=left|For||69,570||90.05 |- |align=left|Against||7,686||9.95 |- |align=left|Invalid/blank votes||2,172||– |- |align=left|'''Total'''||'''79,428'''||'''100.00''' |- |align=left|Registered voters/turnout||103,818||76.51 |- |colspan=3 align=left|Source: [http://cecnkr.am/%D5%A1%D5%B4%D6%83%D5%B8%D6%83%D5%BE%D5%A5%D5%AC-%D5%A5%D5%B6-%D5%B0%D5%A1%D5%B6%D6%80%D5%A1%D6%84%D5%BE%D5%A5%D5%AB-%D5%BE%D5%A5%D6%80%D5%BB%D5%B6%D5%A1%D5%AF%D5%A1%D5%B6-%D5%A1%D6%80%D5%A4%D5%B5/?lang=en CEC] |}
==Reactions== The government of [[Azerbaijan]], which Nagorno-Karabakh is officially part of but which lost ''de facto'' control of the region following the [[Nagorno-Karabakh War]], condemned the referendum calling it a "provocation" and counter-productive for the conflict resolution process.<ref>[http://en.apa.az/nagorno_karabakh/referendum-in-occupied-azerbaijan-lands-another-provocation-of-yerevan.html “Referendum” in occupied Azerbaijan lands – another provocation of Yerevan] Azerbaijan Press Agency, 17 February 2017</ref> The government also issued an international arrest warrant for three [[Member of the European Parliament|Members of the European Parliament]] who acted as observers at the referendum.<ref>[http://www.praguemonitor.com/2017/02/24/mep-%C5%A1t%C4%9Btina-faces-azeri-arrest-warrant MEP Štětina faces Azeri arrest warrant] Prague Daily Monitor, 24 February 2017</ref>
The [[OSCE Minsk Group]], the official mediator of the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict, stated that the results of the referendum would not change the legal status of Nagorno-Karabakh.<ref>[http://www.osce.org/mg/300591 Statement by the Co-Chairs of the OSCE Minsk Group] OCSE, 17 February 2017</ref> The governments of several countries stated that they did not recognise the referendum, including [[Germany]],<ref>[http://vestnikkavkaza.net/news/German-Foreign-Ministry-to-Vestnik-Kavkaza-German-government-does-not-recognize-referendum-in-Nagorno-Karabakh.html German Foreign Ministry to Vestnik Kavkaza: German government does not recognize 'referendum' in Nagorno-Karabakh] Vestnik Kavkaza, 23 February 2017</ref> [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]],<ref>[http://civil.ge/eng/article.php?id=29871 Tbilisi Does not Recognize Nagorno-Karabakh Referendum] Civil, 21 February 2017</ref> [[Ukraine]],<ref>[http://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/404926.html Ukraine considers so-called referendum in Nagorno-Karabakh illegitimate] Interfax, 22 February 2017</ref> and [[Turkey]].<ref>[http://kp.crimea.ua/2017/02/18/turciya-ne-priznaet-referendum-v-nagornom-karabaxe-mid/ Турция не признает «референдум» в Нагорном Карабахе — МИД] KP, 18 February 2017</ref>
