A '''witness statement''' is a [[Signature|signed]] document recording the [[evidence]] of a [[witness]]. A definition used in the UK is "a written statement signed by a person which contains the evidence which that person would be allowed to give orally".<ref>[[Civil Procedure Rules]] (CPR) Rule 32.4</ref>

In the United States, witness statements are generally eschewed in favour of a discovery process including [[Deposition (law)|deposition]] of oral testimony given by key witnesses prior to trial.{{cn|date=September 2016}}

